race.comment: EXTRA ZERO (1) comes here first-up and on the back of a trial win here recently. The blinkers come off for his fresh effort and his form last campaign makes for good reading. Beaten at odds-on his past two before the spell, but that level looks good enough to win this. IN SITU (10) has trialled well coming into his debut but felt the pinch late after being keen through the early stages of the race, tiring out of contention. He'll be better for that effort and the slight drop back in trip may be up his alley. Has the speed to offset the wide draw and can improve. SUMMER MOOD (8) finished off well first-up over the 1200m journey here when coming in without a trial. Can improve on that performance with a better draw and fitness under her belt. Expecting her to be in the finish. REMEMBER WHEN (4) is building nicely this time in and is not to be discounted. DIXIE PRINCESS (7) hasn't been far away in recent races and has to be included.
